      <h1>Getting Started</h1>
      <p>You will need <a href="https://nodejs.org/">node</a> installed as a development dependency.</p>
      <p><a href="https://github.com/Addepar/ember-charts/">Clone it from Github</a>
      or <a href="https://github.com/Addepar/ember-charts/releases">download the ZIP repo</a></p>
      <div class="highlight">
<pre><code>$
$ npm install
$ bower install
$ ember serve</code></pre>
      <p>Go to your browser and navigate to localhost:4200</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
      <hr>
      <h1>Contributing</h1>
      <p>You can contribute to this project in one of two ways:
      <ul class="styled">
        <li>Browse the ember-charts <a href="https://github.com/Addepar/ember-charts/issues?state=open">issues</a> and report bugs</li>
        <li>Clone the ember-charts repo, make some changes according to our development guidelines and issue a pull-request with your changes.</li>
      </ul>
      </p>
      <p>We keep the ember-charts.js code to the minimum necessary, giving users as much control as possible.</p>
